security_findings.evidence:
UNPATCHED SymCryptEckeySetValue (sub_180041b98) - hardcoded doubling:
```c
// r9 = cbPublicKey, caller-derived as 2 * field_element_size
// *(rsi + 0x14) = field_element_size
if (cbPublicKey == *(rsi + 0x14) * 2)   // hardcoded element count 2
    goto proceed;
return 0x800e;  // STATUS_INVALID_PARAMETER
```

PATCHED SymCryptEckeySetValue (sub_180041b50) - table-driven element count:
```c
// arg5 = point-format index (static per-curve; 2 for reachable short-Weierstrass imports)
if (cbPublicKey == SymCryptEcpointFormatNumberofElements[arg5] * *(rsi + 0x14))
    goto proceed;
return 0x800e;  // STATUS_INVALID_PARAMETER
```

The index is computed identically in the callers in BOTH builds:
```c
index = (*(curve_descriptor + 4) != 3) ? 2 : 1;  // 'cmp dword [r8+4], 3; setnz al; inc eax'
```
The callers build a two-coordinate public-key buffer of 2*field_element_size and pass its length as cbPublicKey.
